<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0dfbcd79-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s5983"><num value="5983">§ 5983.</num><heading> Grants authorized; authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0dfbcd7a-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s5983/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Grants authorized</heading><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id0dfbcd7b-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s5983/a/1"><num value="1" class="bold">(1)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">The Secretary is authorized to make grants to eligible entities for the development and implementation of seminars in American government and civics for elementary and secondary school teachers and other educators who work with minority and Native American students.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I79" class="indent3 firstIndent-2" id="id0dfbcd7c-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s5983/a/2"><num value="2" class="bold">(2)</num><heading class="bold"> Award rule</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1">In awarding grants under this subchapter, the Secretary shall ensure that there is wide geographic distribution of such grants.</p>
</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id0dfbcd7d-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s5983/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated $5,000,000 for fiscal 1995, and such sums as may be necessary for each of the fiscal years 1996, 1997, and 1998, to carry out this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id0dfbcd7e-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/227/tVIII/s803">Pub. L. 103–227, title VIII, § 803</ref>, <date date="1994-03-31">Mar. 31, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/210">108 Stat. 210</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
